.csv files are very large, .feather files are of less mb, .parquet is very famous and known for its less size
another format can be .xlsx for excel sheets which has less size than .csv files

#
pd.read_csv('xyz.csv', sep='', names=['',''], index_col=[''], use_cols=['',''] ,header = j, skiprows= [give row index], nrows= j, 
encoding='', error_bad_line= True/ False, dtype={'column_name': data_type}, parse_dates=['column name'], convertor={'abc': convertor},
na_values=['',''], chunksize= j )
pd.read_parquet('xyz.parquet')
pd.read_excel('xyz.xlsx')


-names          --> change the column headings
-index_cols     --> to use other column as index
-use_cols       --> to use the specified columns only
-header         --> to use any specific row as main heading row
-skiprows       --> skip rows
-nrows          --> gives n number of rows randomly
-error_bad_lines --> removes all the rows whose number of entries are more than usual rows
-dtype          --> to change the data type of a specific column
-parse_dates    --> to consider dates as dates or they are considered as strings initially
-convertor       --> to convert specific values of a column 
-na_values      --> considers the listed values as na values and do not consider them
-chunksize      --> breaks data into chunks for easy working


